string.name: sample_desc
string.value: This example demonstrates how to subscribe to and publish common events. Note that this application is released as a system application because it uses the system behavior of releasing sticky events. This feature cannot be used by common third-party applications.

string.name: once_tips
string.value: The following events take effect only in the current running period:

string.name: screen_on_tips
string.value: Do not use your phone. You have turned on the screen.

string.name: screen_off_tips
string.value: Do not use your phone. You have turned off the screen.

string.name: wifi_tips
string.value: Do not use your phone. you have connected or disconnected wifi.

string.name: screen_lock_tips
string.value: Do not use your phone. You have locked the screen.

string.name: screen_unlock_tips
string.value: Do not use your phone. You have unlocked the screen.

string.name: total_interrupt_tips
string.value: Number of interference times during the monitoring period:

string.name: enable_screen_on
string.value: Indicates whether to record the screen-on event.

string.name: enable_screen_locked
string.value: Indicates whether to record the screen-lock events.

string.name: enable_screen_unlocked
string.value: Indicates whether to record the screen-unlock events.

string.name: enable_screen_off
string.value: Indicates whether to record the screen-off event.

string.name: enable_wifi
string.value: Indicates whether to record online events.

string.name: reason_common_event_sticky
string.value: Allow the app to publish sticky public events in common event listening scenarios
